<h3 class="govuk-heading-m">How to find the register URL</h3>

<ol class="govuk-list govuk-list--number govuk-list--spaced">
  <li>
    <strong>Open the CloudFormation console</strong>
    <p class="govuk-body">
      Go to <a href="https://us-east-1.console.aws.amazon.com/cloudformation/home?region=us-east-1#/stacks" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="govuk-link">CloudFormation console in us-east-1<span class="govuk-visually-hidden"> (opens in new tab)</span></a>
    </p>
  </li>

  <li>
    <strong>Find your stack</strong>
    <p class="govuk-body">
      Look for a stack containing <code>digital-planning-register</code> in the name.
      The status should be <span class="govuk-tag govuk-tag--green">CREATE_COMPLETE</span>
    </p>
  </li>

  <li>
    <strong>Go to the Outputs tab</strong>
    <p class="govuk-body">Click the stack name, then select the <strong>Outputs</strong> tab. You'll see:</p>
    <table class="govuk-table">
      <thead class="govuk-table__head">
        <tr class="govuk-table__row">
          <th class="govuk-table__header">Output</th>
          <th class="govuk-table__header">What it is</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody class="govuk-table__body">
        <tr class="govuk-table__row">
          <td class="govuk-table__cell"><code>RegisterUrl</code></td>
          <td class="govuk-table__cell">The register URL (HTTPS via CloudFront)</td>
        </tr>
        <tr class="govuk-table__row">
          <td class="govuk-table__cell"><code>CloudWatchLogsUrl</code></td>
          <td class="govuk-table__cell">Link to application logs</td>
        </tr>
        <tr class="govuk-table__row">
          <td class="govuk-table__cell"><code>ECSClusterUrl</code></td>
          <td class="govuk-table__cell">Link to the ECS cluster console</td>
        </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </li>

  <li>
    <strong>Open the register</strong>
    <p class="govuk-body">
      Click the <code>RegisterUrl</code> value to open the Digital Planning Register. You should see the homepage with a council selection interface.
    </p>
    <p class="govuk-body">
      No login is required — this is a public-facing register designed for residents.
    </p>
  </li>
</ol>

<div class="govuk-inset-text">
  <strong>No login needed:</strong> Unlike the BOPS back-office, the Digital Planning Register is a public application. Residents can browse and search planning applications without creating an account.
</div>
